history.content:
Graduate students are unable in the new system to waitlist for undergraduate classes outside their home department.  As a masters student, your requirement is likely to be for graduate courses in COE.  In any event, no graduate students will be enrolled in CS undergraduate courses when a parallel graduate course is offered alongside it in the same time/space -- in this instance 286A.

Please do not simultaneously post on piazza and email staff. This trend duplicates a lot of work and reduces the number of students we can help.

Graduate students are unable in the new system to waitlist for undergraduate classes outside their home department.  As a masters student, your requirement is likely to be for graduate courses in COE.  In any event, no graduate students will be enrolled in CS undergraduate courses when a parallel graduate course is offered alongside it in the same time/space -- in this instance 286A.

I tried to register CS186 during my adjustment period, but I was getting an error message saying:"Error: Permission to enroll in this class is required. The class falls outside your career of study. Choose another class." 

I am a master ME student, and in my graduate requirement, I am required to register at least 12 units from the college of engineering. 

Does anyone have the same issue?
history.subject: Getting error for Non-CS major student registering CS186
